        <h1>LeetCode 976: Largest Perimeter Triangle (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given an integer array nums, return the largest perimeter of a triangle with a non-zero area, formed
                from three of these lengths. If it is impossible to form any triangle of a non-zero area, return 0.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [2,1,2] → Output: 5. You can form a triangle with sides of length 2, 1, and 2. Input: nums
                = [1,2,1,10] → Output: 0. You cannot use the side of length 10 with any other two sides to form a
                triangle.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int largestPerimeter(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        // Sort the array in descending order to try largest elements first
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end(), greater&lt;int&gt;());
        
        // Check each possible triplet starting from largest elements
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; nums.size() - 2; i++) {
            int a = nums[i];     // largest side
            int b = nums[i + 1]; // second largest side  
            int c = nums[i + 2]; // third largest side
            
            // Triangle inequality: sum of any two sides &gt; third side
            // Since a &gt;= b &gt;= c, we only need to check if b + c &gt; a
            if (b + c &gt; a) {
                return a + b + c;
            }
        }
        
        // No valid triangle found
        return 0;
    }
};</code></pre>
